A perfect example of melted buildings in Switzerland. What now are called 'hobbit houses' were actually buildings that melted through the plasma burning effect of the electric discharge between earth and the destroyer planet. In fact most mountains were probably huge buildings. The bricks that were used to build these huge buildings melted where the plasma heat hit them. Other parts remained untouched (pockets of survival) because the plasma moved over the surface of the earth like lightning in random movement. The melt waters (called the deluge) cooled the melted stone quickly into solid rock.
